Sentencas: A solid-oxide fuel cell that operates at 500 degreesC (instead of 600 degreesC and higher), with lower material cost and better long-term stability, is presented.
Titulo: Novel cathodes for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Its key piece is a cathode made of a silver/copper-doped bismuth vanadate (Ag-BI-CUVOX) composite, which reduces oxygen at lower temperatures and diminishes the resistance between the cathode and the electrolyte.
Titulo: Novel cathodes for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Figure shows an SEM cross section of the described cell.
Titulo: Novel cathodes for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
